description: This project develops a machine learning framework to predict LTE (4G) signal quality metricsRSRP, RSRQ, and SINRusing models trained on suburban and urban environments. It evaluates and compares Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, SVR, and Extra Trees for accurate signal prediction.

A framework for analyzing P2P lending using network centrality metrics and MST-based network analysis, combined with machine learning models (XGBoost, Random Forest, Logistic Regression) to predict loan success and manage risk. Validated on real datasets for improved accuracy and scalability.

Compares base LLMs, as well as fine-tuned frontier and open-sources models, to traditional machine-learning (ML) techniques and human prediction of product prices based on a description. The winner, along with 6 other agents, is productionized in an AI agentic framework that sends push notifications to you when a deal is found.

UTScan is a hybrid machine learning framework that quantifies daily urban travel intensity using continuous seismic noise recordings. Leveraging CatBoost and LSTM, UTScan extracts features from the 220Hz seismic power spectrum to deliver accurate, generalizable travel predictions across regions and time periods.

In this hands-on assignment, I built a neural network using Tensorflow to recognize handwritten digits from the MNIST dataset. To deepen my understanding I implemented the network's forward path in NumPy, revealing the inner workings of machine learning frameworks.
Mathematical optimization and machine learning framework and algorithms.

A framework for developing personalized exoskeleton control parameters using machine learning models trained on biomechanical simulation data. This project integrates OpenSim musculoskeletal modeling with machine learning pipelines to predict optimal assistance parameters based on individual user characteristics.

This project is a multi-agent AI system designed to automatically generate short, trendy tweets based on the latest AI, Machine Learning, and Data Science news. Built using Agno (phidata) framework, it leverages Groq's Llama3-70b model, real-time search via DuckDuckGo Tool, and is hosted with FastAPI for scalability and flexibility.

Framework for spatial selectivity estimation using machine learning and optimizer feedback. Addresses both RCC filters and distance-based filters by transforming estimation into regression task. Compares neural networks, tree-based models and instance-based approaches against traditional RTree and histogram methods across 14 spatial datasets.
